   transmission of data, which are non-constrained, delay-constrained,
   reliability-constrained, and critical. In this context, this paper
   proposes a traffic priority-aware adaptive slot allocation-based medium
   access control (TraySL-MAC) protocol. Firstly, a reduced contention
   adaptive slot allocation algorithm is presented to minimize contention
   rounds. Secondly, a low threshold vital signs criticality-based adaptive
   slot allocation algorithm is developed for high priority data. Thirdly,
