   Technologies},
Year = {2019},
Note = {10th International Conference on Computing, Communication and Networking
   Technologies (ICCCNT), IIT Kanpur, Kanpur, INDIA, JUL 06-08, 2019},
Abstract = {This paper presents a data sensitive adaptive Medium Access Control
   (DSA-MAC) protocol for intra-hospital scenario. Main feature of this
   protocol is to prioritize the node, based on sensitivity of data it has
   to communicate. Recent advancements in Wireless Body Area Network (WBAN)
   supported biomedical sensors, have given new direction to the health
   monitoring techniques. In wireless body area network, multiple
   biomedical sensors are planted on/in the patient's body which is
   wirelessly linked to the network. The standard protocol such as IEEE
   802.15.4 for body area network (BAN) cannot fulfil all the requirements
   as they do not assist or maintain prioritized and varied data transfer
   requirements of various medical sensor nodes. This paper proposes a
   DSA-MAC protocol by prioritizing the available medical sensor data for
   channel allocation. The performance analysis of DSA-MAC shows that it
