   area network coordinator to assimilate the data sent by the sensor
   nodes. Tier-2 has Wi-Fi as a bridge to transfer the vital data to the
   hospital information system located in tier -3. As both the networking
   techniques (ZigBee and Wi-Fi) use the same 2.4 Citlz Industrial,
   Scientific, and Medical (ISM) band, which leads to the coexistence
   issue. This paper deals with the interference analysis and modeling of
   MAC protocols for the coexistence of ZigBee and Wi-li for a hospital
   centered wireless body area network (HCWBAN). Various network simulation
   models arc executed for their Clear Channel Assessment (CCA) mode and
   total number of nodes in the model. An exhaustive investigation is done
