Abstract = {Emergency nodes, i.e, nodes with priority 7 as per 802.15.6 standard
   play a very important role in facilitating the immediate transfer of
   information during life threatening situations. These nodes should relay
   critical information with utmost reliability and in the shortest
   possible time. IEEE 802.15.6 provides the necessary functionality to
   these nodes by adapting the contention window sizes as well as the time
   duration over which it can transmit in a superframe. Although these
   methods solve problems when emergency nodes are few in number,
